         <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">

<ab><lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἑρμογένης">Ἑρμογένης</name>  <persName type="attested"><name nymRef="#Ἑρμογένης">Ἑρμογένους</name></persName></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸ</w> <w lemma="ἐπιστύλιον">ἐπιστύλιον</w><lb n="2"/> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὸν</w> <w lemma="ἐπί">ἐπ'</w> <w lemma="αὐτός">αὐτοῦ</w> <w lemma="κόσμος">κόσμον</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῶι</w> <w lemma="δῆμος">Δήμωι</w></ab>
</div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>Hermogenes son of Hermogenes, the epistyle and the decoration on it for the People.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>This is one of a group of such texts, almost  all found re-used near the South-east Gate, dedicating an <term>epistylion</term>, with its decoration (<term>kosmos</term>) to the Demos: <ref type="inscription" n="1126" target="120405.xml"/> (=CIG 2752), <ref type="inscription" n="1103" target="120503.xml"/> (=LBW 1589), <ref type="inscription" n="1104" target="120504.xml"/> (= LBW 1591), <ref type="inscription" n="1127" target="120505.xml"/> (=MAMA 439), <ref type="inscription" n="1128" target="120506.xml"/> (=MAMA 440), <ref type="inscription" n="1129" target="130503.xml"/> (=MAMA 441), <ref type="inscription" n="1130" target="120406.xml"/> (=MAMA 442), <ref type="inscription" n="1131" target="120407.xml"/> (=MAMA 443), <ref type="inscription" n="1132" target="120408.xml"/> (=MAMA 442), <ref type="inscription" n="1133" target="120404.xml"/> (= Reinach 127 and 128).</p>
            <p>The group discussed by<bibl n="jmr1990">
                  <author>Reynolds</author>, 'Inscriptions and the Building of the Temple', <title>Aphrodisias Papers </title>(Ann Arbor, 1990), 37-40, 39.</bibl>.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p>Published by <bibl n="CIGII">Boeckh, from Sherard papers, <citedRange>2751</citedRange>
               </bibl>; published by <bibl n="fellows1841">Fellows, <citedRange>15</citedRange>
               </bibl>, whence <bibl n="bailie1846">Bailie <citedRange>70</citedRange>
               </bibl>; published by <bibl n="LBW">Waddington, LBW <citedRange>1590</citedRange>
               </bibl>; published by <bibl n="reinach">Reinach, from Gaudin's squeeze, <citedRange>129</citedRange>
               </bibl>; published by <bibl n="MAMA8">Cormack, from the MAMA records, <citedRange>439</citedRange>
               </bibl>, whence <bibl n="PHI">
                  <author>McCabe</author>
                  <title level="m">PHI Aphrodisias</title>
                  <citedRange n="256962">84</citedRange>
               </bibl>.</p>
         </div>
